      "source": [
        "## Define and Train the Autoencoder Model\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "Autoencoder architecture built in this block:\n",
        "\n",
        "*   Encoder compresses input data into a lower dimensional representation for the autoencoder to digest.\n",
        "*   Decoder will learn from this compressed data and reconstruct the original input to learn what a normal transaction representation would look like.\n",
        "\n",
        "Encoder learns solely on the data from **Normal Transactions** [Class = 0]\n",
        "\n",
        "Fraudulant Transactions will have higher error because model taught itself on normal data\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 585
        },
        "id": "54e7cfd4",
        "outputId": "a4897525-8ba5-44aa-d066-6901a7fa8412"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Define the autoencoder model\n",
        "input_dim = X_train.shape[1] # Number of features\n",
        "encoding_dim = 14 # Latent dimension\n",
        "\n",
        "# Encoder architecture\n",
        "input_layer = Input(shape=(input_dim,))\n",
        "encoder = Dense(encoding_dim, activation=\"tanh\")(input_layer)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Decoder architecture\n",
        "decoder = Dense(input_dim, activation=\"tanh\")(encoder)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Autoencoder model\n",
        "autoencoder = Model(inputs=input_layer, outputs=decoder)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compile the autoencoder\n",
        "autoencoder.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mean_squared_error')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Model summary\n",
        "autoencoder.summary()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the autoencoder on normal transactions\n",
        "history = autoencoder.fit(X_train,\n",
        "                          X_train,\n",
        "                          epochs=10,\n",
        "                          batch_size=32,\n",
        "                          shuffle=True,\n",
        "                          validation_data=(X_val, X_val),\n",
        "                          verbose=1).history"
      ],
